Mandate thief Buhari said he’ll only appoint people “I personally know” as ministers, which is another telltale signal of impending in-your-face nepotism and subnationalism. Nonetheless, if personal familiarity with him is the sole criterion for appointing ministers, what’s taking him so long? What’s difficult about appointing his relatives, friends, and acquaintances as ministers? This man represents the worst of Nigeria, the personification of the vilest form of incompetence. Source: Facebook